title: Interaction of 26 MeV deuterons with C-12.

x4freetext: Interaction of 26 MeV deuterons with C-12.

x4codes.hlp: Nat`l Inst. for Nucl. and High Energy Physics, Sect.K, Netherlands

x4freetext: Polyethylene (CH2)n target was used with a scattering
angle greater than 90 degree. At small angles self-
supporting graphite foils of about 60 mum and 10 mum
have been used. The 60 mum target was made on a lathe
by turning a vacuum-sucked piece of pure graphite.
The 10 mum target was obtained by using a sputtering
technique whereby a carbon-arc was drawn in vacuum
under a horizontal glass plate covered with a dried
soapfilm. The number of carbon atoms per cm**2 of the
(CH2)n target was determined by weighing. For other
targets this was done by comparison of yield
measurements with measurements done the (CH2)n target.

x4codes.hlp: Nat`l Inst. for Nucl. and High Energy Physics, Sect.K, Netherlands

x4freetext: The detector consisted of a 0.2 mm
thick CsI(Tl) crystal and a 6 mm  thick NaI(Tl)
scintillation counter.
.The solid state detector was a p-i-n type
lithium-drifted silicon counter of 2.2 mm thickness,
in which a proton could dissipate an energy of
approximately 20 MeV as a maximum.
The dead-time correction was made.
The systematic errors in the absolute values of the
differential cross section is about 6%. This error
is mainly due to uncertainty in the target thickness
determination and the error in the charge measurement.
Errors due to finite geometry and multiple scattering
were estimated to be small compared to the other
uncertainties.
